HEADWORD: Sesquipedality
<hw>Ses`qui*pe*dal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or condition of being sesquipedal.</def>
<rj><au>Sterne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The use of sesquipedalian words; style characterized
by the use of long words; sesquipedalism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sesquiplicate</ent>⟦br⟧
